        "abstract": "Vaccines directed against the outer surface protein A (OspA) of B. burgdorferi have been applied to rodents either via direct inoculation (Tsao et al., 2004) or as baits containing spirochetal OspA (Meirelles Richer, Aroso, Con tente-Cu orno, Ivanova, & GomesSolecki, 2011). [...]rodent-targeted baits containing antibiotics that clear rodents and ticks of spirochetes have also been tested in the lab and the field (Dolan et al., 2011). The efficacy of doxycycline prophylaxis was judged to be 87%, but how widely physicians practice this method is presently unknown. [...]many approaches are available for preventing Lyme disease, but the incidence nevertheless continues to climb.",
